# Command: point x y [cs]
# Arguments:
#    'x'  (int) x coordinate of the point
#    'y'  (int) y coordinate of the point
#    'cs' (int)[optional] cross size
# Description: Draws a point on the canvas
# Note: If the 'cs' parameter is not passed, then this will
#       simply paint a pixel on the screen. The 'cs' parameter
#       specifies a cross size of the point.
# Use example:
bounds 210 210 center invert_y
stroke 0.3;color 200 200 200;grid 200 200 10 10
color 0 0 0; stroke 1
# Example starts
point  0  0
point  5  5
point -5 -5
point  5 -5
point -5  5
point  40  50  2
point  40 -50  2
point -70  20 32
point -30 -40 15
# There's no real need to align the numbers...
